## Public Constructors

### BTFTypeFuncProto() {#a1a3bb6bf3128ed00fd08865d079eee9c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>BTFTypeFuncProto::BTFTypeFuncProto (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/disubroutinetype">DISubroutineType</a> &#42; STy, uint32&#95;t VLen, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> std::unordered&#95;map&lt; uint32&#95;t, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> &gt; &amp; FuncArgNames)</>}>
The Func kind represents both subprogram and pointee of function pointers.

If the FuncName is empty, it represents a pointee of function pointer. Otherwise, it represents a subprogram. The func arg names are empty for pointee of function pointer case, and are valid names for subprogram.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/bpf/btfdebug-h/#l00149">149</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/bpf/btfdebug-h">BTFDebug.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/bpf/btfdebug-cpp/#l00340">340</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/bpf/btfdebug-cpp">BTFDebug.cpp</a>.
